The Ordinance provides a power density limit (in W/m^2), and the electric field (in V/m) is a derived plane wave equivalent value

The regulation sets limits for power density at 70% of those in the EU Recommendation (ICNIRP 98) (48.8) and 60% when antenna stations are located closer than 300 metres from the property boundaries of schools, kindergartens, hospitals or eldercare facilities (45.1).

3 V/m: limit per antenna for schools and hospitals (for hospitals a 3 V/m limit (not frequency dependent) is required inside the building for EMC reasons); 14.5 V/m: limit for a single installation; 58 V/m: limit for cumulative exposure from multiple antenna locations. The total exposure cannot exceed ICNIRP and per antenna it should not exceed 1/4 of ICNIRP field limits (1/16 power density).

The exposure limit is 20 V/m. Moreover, in homes, schools, playgrounds and places where people may stay for longer than 4 hours,  an 'attention value' of 6 V/m is applied and averaged over any 24 hour period. A 'quality goal' for new installations is identical to the attention value.
